text.tspan: Now you have done your training trial.
The real test begins now. Concentrate!
Click the mouse button anywhere to continue
In this experiment you will try to memorize numbers
you see on the screen. All numbers are between
0 and 9. We call such numbers digits.
You will see a sequence of digits, one after another.
Once you have remembered the digits, you need to repeat them.
You see a key pad on the screen (see image). Use the mouse to click them
in the same order as they were shown.
If you make a mistake, you can "clear" the last one you entered.
After you have entered all the letters,
The computer will tell you if you
remembered the letters correctly or not.
You will have to remember several sequences.
The sequence of letters will get longer until you can no longer
At the end of the experiment, you will get your total score.
The total score is known as the digit span.
